        <mxCell id="table" value="&lt;b&gt;Rank&lt;/b&gt; | &lt;b&gt;Model (NVIDIA free endpoint)&lt;/b&gt; | &lt;b&gt;Agentic SWE fit&lt;/b&gt; | &lt;b&gt;Benchmark availability&lt;/b&gt; | &lt;b&gt;Recommendation&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;1 | step-3.5-flash | Best overall balance (speed + coding + reliability) | No endpoint-specific public score | Use as default agent model&#xa;2 | qwen3.5-122b-a10b | Strong reasoning/coding, slower than Step | Model-family benchmarks available; endpoint-specific not public | Use for deep analysis tasks&#xa;3 | nvidia-reasoning (DeepSeek-R1 based) | Excellent reasoning, high latency | Public DeepSeek-R1 benchmark papers exist; endpoint-specific not public | Use for hard reasoning, not chat loops&#xa;4 | minimax-m2.1 | Fast conversational model, weaker SWE depth | Limited transparent SWE benchmark data | Use for lightweight helper tasks" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#334155;fontColor=#0F172A;fontSize=14;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
